esirable FEF\nand that, at the same time, are mechanically stable by presence of substrate\ntip. Finally, we also discuss the validity of Schottky's conjecture (SC) for\nthese systems showing that, while to obey SC is a indicative of scale\ninvariance, the opposite is not necessarily satisfied. This suggest that a\ncareful analysis must be done before attribute the SC as a origin of giant FEF\nin experiments.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Jul 2016 18:45:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 1 Aug 2016 14:21:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-30"}
