{"id":"1607.07491","submitter":"Jan Kyn\\v{c}l","authors":"Josef Cibulka and Jan Kyn\\v{c}l","title":"Better upper bounds on the F\\\"uredi-Hajnal limits of permutations","comments":"30 pages, 4 figures; new Section 7","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO cs.DM","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A binary matrix is a matrix with entries from the set $\\{0,1\\}$. We say that\na binary matrix $A$ contains a binary matrix $S$ if $S$ can be obtained from\n$A$ by removal of some rows, some columns, and changing some $1$-entries to\n$0$-entries. If $A$ does not contain $S$, we say that $A$ avoids $S$. A\n$k$-permutation matrix $P$ is a binary $k \\times k$ matrix with exactly one\n$1$-entry in every row and one $1$-entry in every column.\n  The F\\\"uredi-Hajnal conjecture, proved by Marcus and Tardos, states that for\nevery permutation matrix $P$, there is a constant $c_P$ such that for every $n\n\\in \\mathbb{N}$, every $n \\times n$ binary matrix $A$ with at least $c_P n$\n$1$-entries contains $P$.\n  We show that $c_P \\le 2^{O(k^{2/3}\\log^{7/3}k / (\\log\\log k)^{1/3})}$\nasymptotically almost surely for a random $k$-permutation matrix $P$. We also\nshow that $c_P \\le 2^{(4+o(1))k}$ for every $k$-permutation matrix $P$,\nimproving the constant in the exponent of a recent upper bound on $c_P$ by Fox.\nMoreover, we improve the upper bound on $c_P$ in terms of the Stanley-Wilf\nlimit $s_P$ to $c_P \\le O\\big(s_P^{2.75} \\log s_P\\big)$.\n  We also consider a higher-dimensional generalization of the Stanley-Wilf\nconjecture about the number of $d$-dimensional $n$-permutation matrices\navoiding a fixed $d$-dimensional $k$-permutation matrix, and prove almost\nmatching upper and lower bounds of the form $(2^k)^{O(n)} \\cdot\n(n!)^{d-1-1/(d-1)}$ and $n^{-O(k)} k^{\\Omega(n)} \\cdot (n!)^{d-1-1/(d-1)}$,\nrespectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Jul 2016 21:36:36 GMT"},{"versi