rgitation strongly affect hemodynamics, followed by\nmitral stenosis, while aortic stenosis has the least impact among the analyzed\nvalvular diseases. The proposed approach can provide new mechanistic insights\nas to which valvular pathologies merit more aggressive treatment of AF. Present\nfindings, if clinically confirmed, hold the potential to impact AF management\n(e.g., adoption of a rhythm control strategy) in specific valvular diseases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Jul 2016 09:29:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-27"}
